plt.bar(["With Pooling", "Without Pooling"],
        [cnn_history["test_acc"], cnn_no_pool_history["test_acc"]])
plt.ylabel("Test Accuracy")
plt.title("Effect of Removing Pooling Layers")
plt.grid(axis='y')
plt.show()

"""### Observation on Removing Pooling Layers

After removing pooling layers, the accuracy decreases.  
This shows that pooling is important in CNN.  

Pooling helps reduce the size of feature maps and keeps important information.  
It also makes the model more stable and easier to train.  

Without pooling, the model becomes heavy and less efficient,  
so the performance reduces.
"""



